# Epic close (automatic)

**Do not wait for the user to ask.** When the last in-scope feature of an epic meets acceptance (Tier 1 green + applicable Tier 2 / manual smoke; cuts already recorded), run **epic close** in the same session (or at the start of the next turn if the ship commit already landed).

## Quality gates (required — reuse handoff checklist)

Epic close **includes** [.cursor/rules/handoff-checklist.mdc](handoff-checklist.mdc). Run those steps first and record results in the close note:

1. Code review (code-reviewer)
2. Tech debt evaluation (tech-debt-evaluator) → update `TECH_DEBT.md` as needed
3. Tests / coverage (merge-ready command from `AGENT_HANDOFF.md` / `TEST_PLAN.md`)
4. Project readiness (optional / N/A)
5. Security review when relevant (security-reviewer)
6. Tier 2 when the epic’s behavior requires it

Do **not** treat epic close as docs-only and skip review, debt, or tests.

## Then status close

Follow [.cursor/skills/pm-governance/SKILL.md](../skills/pm-governance/SKILL.md) → *Epic close*: mark the epic/phase complete in `PM_PLAN` / product plan, sync `doc/PROJECT_STATUS.md` + `AGENT_HANDOFF.md` → *Current state*, write the close/handoff note, commit/push per github-feature-workflow, summarize for the user.

## Do not auto-do on close

- Start the next epic’s implementation unless the user already asked or **Next** already directed it.
- Retire prototypes / dual trees or other deferred debt unless the user or plan **Next** says so this session.
- Re-open explicitly cut features.
